# How to use this pack

This document is your website copy deck. Each page below contains finished, on-brand text you (or your designer) can drop straight into the new site - headings, body copy, button labels and form fields. Green callout boxes marked "Website copy" are the literal words intended to appear on the page. Plain paragraphs are guidance and rationale for you.

## What the best IT websites do - and what we copied

We benchmarked your redesign against IT and B2B sites widely cited for clarity. A few patterns drive everything below:

- Answer three questions in five seconds - what you do, who you serve, and why it matters. Vague taglines like "Empowering Digital Transformation" were avoided in favour of specific, outcome-led lines (the Cloudflare / Linear / Vercel approach).
- Sell outcomes, not features - every service is framed as a business result (time saved, cost cut, compliance gained), then backed by a proof metric. Feature lists sit underneath, not on top.
- One clear action per screen - specific CTAs such as "Book a Discovery Call" and "Get a Free Assessment" convert far better than "Contact Us" or "Learn More".
- Trust, made visible - recognitions (Startup India, KSUM, K-SPACE), 140+ projects, partner network and security posture are used as credibility anchors, the way Atlassian shows customer counts and Datadog shows client logos.
- Serve every buyer - government, banking, enterprise and SME visitors each get a clear path, because B2B decisions involve several stakeholders with different questions.

**REFERENCE SITES WORTH SHOWING YOUR DESIGNER**

Cloudflare and Linear (hero clarity + single CTA), Vercel (technical clarity), Atlassian and Datadog (social proof / logos), HubSpot (transparent, benefit-led solution pages), Snyk and HPE (making complex offerings instantly understandable). Regional benchmarks for clean product storytelling: Zoho and Freshworks.

